Camden.Woodrow Wilson High School (New Jersey):
Woodrow Wilson High School is a four-year public high school in the City of Camden, in Camden County, New Jersey, United States, serving students in ninth through twelfth grades as part of the Camden City Public Schools.
As of the 2014-15 school year, the school had an enrollment of 905 students and 70.5 classroom teachers (on an FTE basis), for a student–teacher ratio of 12.8:1. There were 762 students (84.2% of enrollment) eligible for free lunch and 14 (1.5% of students) eligible for reduced-cost lunch.
